\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish mandatory governance and internal controls for the financial stewardship and procurement of Elko County technology resources.
 This policy enforces a strict separation between 
\series bold
Technical Authority
\series default
 (validation of need,
 compatibility,
 lifecycle impact,
 inventory integration,
 and security) and 
\series bold
Financial Authority
\series default
 (budget verification and lawful purchasing execution).
 This separation is required to prevent unauthorized technology acquisition (“Shadow IT”),
 ensure value realization,
 and maintain full auditability of public funds in accordance with Nevada Revised Statutes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all technology-related financial transactions conducted by any Elko County entity,
 department,
 or elected office,
 regardless of funding source or purchasing mechanism.
 This includes,
 but is not limited to:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Hardware,
 software,
 and infrastructure procurement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Cloud services (SaaS,
 IaaS,
 PaaS),
 subscriptions,
 renewals,
 and auto-renewals.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Consulting,
 support,
 and managed service contracts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Technology purchases made via Departmental Purchase Cards (P-Cards),
 regardless of the funding source.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Grant-funded technology acquisitions and renewals.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Technical Approval
\series default
:
 Shall act as technical authority and shall approve technical specifications,
 security requirements,
 and lifecycle/architecture impact for all technology purchases prior to the obligation of funds,
 execution of purchasing actions,
 or acceptance of contract terms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Vendor Governance
\series default
:
 Shall serve as the primary owner for County IT vendor technical standards,
 security requirements,
 and technical dispute escalation activities delegated to the Information Operations Department.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Delegation
\series default
:
 Shall designate technical approvers only through 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Delegation of Authority) and shall ensure such delegations are documented.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Workflow Execution
\series default
:
 Shall execute day-to-day procurement workflow tasks (e.g.,
 requisitions,
 tracking,
 receiving coordination) as directed by the IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Audit Readiness
\series default
:
 Shall maintain procurement tracking artifacts required for audit and reconciliation,
 including the linkage of purchases to requisitions,
 receiving records,
 work orders/tickets,
 project codes,
 and inventory/CMDB entries.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Fiscal Affairs (Financial Authority)
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Verification
\series default
:
 Shall verify budget availability and execute purchasing and payment activities in accordance with applicable County procurement rules and NRS 332.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Gatekeeper Function
\series default
:
 Shall not process technology invoices,
 reimbursements,
 or payment requests that lack documented Technical Approval from the IT Director or a formally delegated technical approver.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Department Heads / Elected Offices
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Requirement Definition
\series default
:
 Shall define business requirements and coordinate with the Information Operations Department for technology needs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Restriction
\series default
:
 Shall not negotiate with technology vendors,
 authorize technology procurement,
 or accept/execute technology contract terms (including click-through terms,
 EULAs,
 MSAs,
 SOWs,
 renewals,
 or auto-renewals) without Information Operations Department review and documented Technical Approval.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
