\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 The Technical–Fiscal Handshake
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Elko County shall employ a mandatory two-step validation for all technology spending:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Technical Approval (Information Operations Department)
\series default
:
 Validation that the request meets County standards.
 Technical Approval shall be valid only when recorded as a distinct approval status within the Department's designated System of Record (CMDB/Service Desk).
 Email correspondence or verbal assent shall not constitute Technical Approval.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Financial Approval (Fiscal Affairs)
\series default
:
 Validates budget availability and ensures purchasing actions comply with applicable procurement requirements (including competitive bidding thresholds and required documentation).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Restrictions
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
A budget line item does not constitute authorization to procure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Fiscal Affairs shall not process payment without documented Technical Approval.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The Information Operations Department shall not integrate,
 support,
 or onboard technology resources that were acquired without documented Technical Approval.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Procurement Controls and “Shadow IT” Prohibition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Centralized Procurement
\series default
:
 All County software,
 hardware,
 and cloud subscriptions shall be procured through the Information Operations Department to ensure security review,
 asset tagging,
 license compliance,
 and inventory/CMDB integration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
P-Card Restrictions
\series default
:
 The use of departmental P-Cards for technology hardware,
 software,
 or subscriptions is prohibited without written pre-authorization by the IT Director (or formally delegated technical approver).
 Fiscal Affairs shall flag suspected technology P-Card transactions for review and audit.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Grant-Funded Technology
\series default
:
 Grant-funded technology is subject to the same standards as County-funded assets,
 including security requirements,
 inventory/CMDB entry,
 supportability,
 and lifecycle cost planning.
 Departments shall engage the Information Operations Department during grant application development to validate feasibility and total cost of ownership.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Auto-Renewal Controls
\series default
:
 Technology subscriptions shall not auto-renew without Technical Approval.
 Where feasible,
 auto-renewal shall be disabled,
 and renewals shall be reviewed in advance to prevent unmanaged commitments.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Bid Splitting
\series default
:
 Splitting a single requirement into multiple smaller transactions to evade competitive bidding thresholds (NRS 332) is strictly prohibited.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Budgeting and Security Allocation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Security Resourcing
\series default
:
 The Information Operations Department shall plan,
 request,
 and maintain discrete funding necessary to implement required security controls and compliance obligations (NIST PM-3,
 SA-2).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Lifecycle Forecasting
\series default
:
 Budget submissions shall include Total Cost of Ownership (TCO) considerations,
 including licensing,
 maintenance,
 support,
 required security controls,
 power/cooling (as applicable),
 and disposal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Asset Integration Controls
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
To preserve inventory integrity and ensure auditability of technology assets and services:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Receiving Control
\series default
:
 Technology shipments shall be directed to the Information Operations Department (or a designated receiving process approved by the IT Director) for inspection and inventory capture.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
No Tag,
 No Pay
\series default
:
 Hardware invoices shall not be approved for payment until assets are received,
 inspected,
 tagged in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 and entered into the CMDB and/or asset inventory per 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
No Registration,
 No Pay
\series default
:
 Software and SaaS invoices shall not be approved for payment until the subscription/license is recorded in the designated license management process and the vendor/service has completed required supply chain review steps per 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Vendor Integrity and Security Addendums
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Conflict of Interest and Gifts
\series default
:
 Personnel participating in procurement decisions shall comply with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Conflicts of interest shall be disclosed and managed.
 Gifts or gratuities from vendors are prohibited where County ethics rules apply.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Contract Security Requirements
\series default
:
 Contracts involving County data exchange,
 hosting,
 or access to County systems shall include required security and data protection terms as defined by Information Operations standards and applicable County contract requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJIS Requirement (Contractors)
\series default
:
 When a vendor/contractor may have logical or physical access to Criminal Justice Information (CJI):
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate

\lang english
The contract shall incorporate the 
\series bold
CJIS Security Addendum
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\lang english
The contracting agency shall ensure each contractor employee with CJI access is provided a copy of the 
\series bold
CJIS Security Addendum
\series default
 and the 
\series bold
CJIS Security Policy
\series default
,
 and executes the 
\series bold
Security Addendum Certification
\series default
 acknowledging receipt and agreement to comply,
 consistent with 
\series bold
CJIS Security Policy 5.1.1.5
\series default
 and 
\series bold
Appendix H
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\lang english
The contracting agency shall retain executed certifications/acknowledgments and ensure they remain available for audit purposes.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Records Retention
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Procurement and procurement-related records shall be retained in accordance with the 
\series bold
Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedule
\series default
 and applicable County retention requirements.
 At a minimum,
 procurement records shall be retained for the period required to support audits,
 claims,
 litigation holds,
 and statutory retention obligations.
\end_layout

